  • Method Details

    • setTagsservice

      public Set<TagEntity> setTagsservice(String[] tags, EventRequest request)
      The setTagsservice function takes in a String array of tags and an EventRequest object. It then creates a new Set of EventEntities, adds the event from the request to it, creates two new Sets: one for all existing TagEntities and one for the return value. Then it iterates through each tag in tags, checks if that tag already exists as a TagEntity (if so add its events to this set), otherwise create a new TagEntity with that tag name and add its events to this set. Finally save each entity into ret before returning it.
      Parameters:
      String - [] tags Get the tags from the front end
      EventRequest - request Get the id of the event that is being updated
      Returns:
      A set<tagentity>

    • eventregister

      public EventResponse eventregister(EventRequest request, String email)
      The eventregister function takes in an EventRequest object and a String email, and returns an EventResponse object. The function first creates a new event entity using the information from the request, then saves it to the database. It then returns an EventResponse with all of its fields filled out.
      Parameters:
      EventRequest - request Get the data from the frontend
      String - email Get the user who is currently logged in

    • registerToEvent

      public String registerToEvent(EventRequest request)
      The registerToEvent function takes an EventRequest object as input and returns a String. The function checks if the user is already registered to the event, and if not it registers him/her.
      Parameters:
      EventRequest - request Get the email and id of the user that wants to register to an event
      Returns:
      A string

    • unregisterToEvent

      public String unregisterToEvent(EventRequest request)
      The unregisterToEvent function takes in an EventRequest object and returns a String. The function finds the event with the id specified in the request, then removes from that event's list of subscribed users, the user whose email is specified in request. If this removal was successful, it returns "successfully unregistered", otherwise it returns "unregistration failed". It does not return anything if there is no such event or user.
      Parameters:
      EventRequest - request Get the id of the event and email of user
      Returns:
      A string

    • updateEvent

      public String updateEvent(EventRequest request)
      The updateEvent function takes an EventRequest object as input and updates the event with the same id in the database. If any of the fields are different from those in the database, they will be updated. for tags is necessary to adopt different way because of the manytomany db relationship.
      Parameters:
      EventRequest - request Get the id of the event to be deleted
      Returns:
      The string "successfully updated" if the update is successful

    • searchEvent

      public List<EventEntity> searchEvent(EventSearchRequest request)
      The searchEvent function takes in a request object and returns a list of EventEntity objects. The function first creates an arraylist of sets, which will be used to store the results from each search. Then it adds the results from searching for title, date range, place and tags into this arraylist. It then creates a set that contains all events in the database (allSet). This is done so that we can use retainAll() on it later on to get only those events that match all search criteria. We then iterate through our arraylist of sets and call retainAll() on allSet with
      Parameters:
      EventSearchRequest - request Get the search parameters from the user
      Returns:
      A list of evententity objects, but the searchtitle function returns a set of evententity objects
